cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL 

The paper proposes a novel algorithm for the solution of mean-payoff games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm involves merging two concepts introduced in the context of parity games, which are closely related to mean-payoff games. These concepts are small progress measures (cs.DS) and quasi dominions (cs.LO). The algorithm also involves optimization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Therefore, these five categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
